                <h1>Who Wrote the Book of Romans? Discover the Author!</h1>
                <p>The Book of Romans, a foundational text of Christian theology, was written by the Apostle Paul. Addressed to the Christians in Rome, this letter outlines key doctrines, including justification by faith and the grace of God. It serves as both a theological treatise and practical guide for living a Christian life.</p>
